  "texts": [
    "G1 and G2 are independently trained to generate high-fidelity synthetic images of benign and malignant lung nodules.",
    "This separation allows each generator to concentrate on the unique attributes of its assigned class, such as smooth edges for benign nodules or irregular, spiculated patterns for malignant nodules.",
    "D1 and D2 act as evaluators, distinguishing between real and synthetic images while emphasizing critical features unique to their respective classes.",
    "The outputs of the discriminators are incorporated through a feature fusion mechanism, incorporating discriminatory information into an attentive feature map.",
    "This map improves the classification procedure by encapsulating subtle elements."
  ],
